nd developers.\n\n*   **Grok Teams:** Empowers small-to-medium organizations with dedicated workspaces, secure sharing, enhanced privacy, and admin controls. Data is kept private and not used for training.\n*   **Grok Business:** Subscription-based offering for organizations to access Grok models for internal business applications and workflows.\n*   **Grok Enterprise:** Subscription-based offering similar to Grok Business, designed for enterprise-grade deployment.\n*   **Grok API:** Provides programmatic access to Grok models (reasoning, vision, tool-use, image generation, voice AI, search). Features include agentic workflows, custom allocations, secure authentication, and dedicated support. Pricing is **not included in advertising rates** and follows its own model (consumption-based, up to one-year terms).\n\n### **Key Details on Usage-Based Pricing & Monetization**\n*   **API Pricing Model:** Revenue from Grok API access is recognized "ratably over the contract term... for stand-ready access or as services are consumed for usage-based arrangements."\n*   **Enterprise Pricing Models:** Grok Business and Enterprise are sold on **license-, consumption-, or outcome-based pricing models**.\n*   **No Mention of Free Tier for Grok:** The excerpts do not disclose a free subscription tier for the Grok product itself. However, basic Grok features are integrated into the X platform, accessible to all users.',
