r the AI business are based on internal and third-party estimates that may prove inaccurate.\n*   **Regulatory Uncertainty:** Evolving global regulatory frameworks for AI, data privacy, and digital platforms could require costly modifications, restrict features, or limit distribution and monetization.\n\n### Supply Chain & Infrastructure Risks\n*   **Critical Component Dependencies:** Scaling AI products relies on a limited number of suppliers for critical components like AI processors (GPUs) and power. Disruptions, shortages, or price increases could severely impact operations and growth.\n*   **Orbital Infrastructure Risks:** The company\'s mention of "orbital AI compute infrastructure" introduces unique risks related to the deployment and operation of space-based systems.',
